======================================================================
REFINED QUESTION: Why does source δ land in B₁?
======================================================================
Checking the actual Ω₂ computation method...

For source v:
  ALL paths (v,b,c) are TT (since v→c automatically)
  Ω₂ condition: ∂₁∘∂₂ = 0 is AUTOMATIC for TT paths
  So relative Ω₂ = span{(v,b,c) : b→c in T\v} / Ω₂(T\v)
  = ALL combinations of source-v TT triples

For interior v:
  Some paths (a,b,c) using v are NT (the skipped face is NOT an arc)
  Ω₂ condition imposes NONTRIVIAL constraints on NT path coefficients
  This couples the three position types and constrains relative Ω₂

======================================================================
NT/TT counts for interior vs source paths
======================================================================

Source vertex (d⁺=n-1):
  TT=6, NT=0: 320 cases

Interior vertex (1 ≤ d⁺ ≤ n-2):
  TT=2, NT=12: 120 cases
  TT=3, NT=9: 800 cases
  TT=4, NT=6: 1680 cases
  TT=5, NT=3: 1440 cases
  TT=6, NT=0: 440 cases

======================================================================
KEY INSIGHT SUMMARY
======================================================================

For source v (d⁺=n-1):
  - ALL paths through v are TT → Ω₂ condition is automatic
  - v only at position 0 → limited boundary structure
  - δ-image is a balanced flow on T\v → can land in B₁
  - RESULT: δ can fail to be injective

For interior v (1 ≤ d⁺ ≤ n-2):
  - Some paths through v are NT → Ω₂ condition CONSTRAINS coefficients
  - v at positions 0, 1, AND 2 → diverse boundary structure
  - δ-image mixes contributions from all position types → harder to be 0
  - RESULT: δ is always injective (HYP-249)

The proof strategy should show:
  (A) The Ω₂ constraint on NT paths using v COUPLES different positions
  (B) This coupling prevents δ from mapping everything to B₁(T\v)
  (C) Specifically: if δ(z) ∈ B₁, the NT coupling forces z ∈ im(∂₃^rel)

This is analogous to how "mixed-type" constraints in linear programming
prevent degeneracy — the diversity of constraint types ensures full rank.

Done.
